runs.comm: golden for Vincent as he top-edges a hook straight down Gilchrist's throat
on middle and leg, paddled off the hips, a tuck really, to short midwicket
a bit of swing away, left alone
on leg, How lifts his arms as the ball crashes into him, high
corker, jaffa, and other such synonyms for pearler, that one pitching just outside off and jinks away
driven to mid-off
right across the right hander, left alone
booming wide down leg, swinging more and more
steps down the track to defend forward on the front foot
pushed across the right hander again, a bit swipe of a cut, but that's a wide
tighter, but still movement away, nonetheless he shoulders arms
a thick outside edge runs up and was on its way before Noffke ran round to tidy up
tight on off, the ball poked to cover, and Symonds flings down the stumps, or should I say stump, his underarm throw at full stretch takes the one stick he had to aim for at the non-striker's
another run-out chance for Symonds but this time he misfields
down leg, helped round there
tighter ball this time, defended on the back foot in line with off
How off the mark with a steer down to third man
hostile bouncer brushes past his nose
tidy delivery, cuts him in half as it nips back in off the seam, and that's through Gilchrist
quality six, flat off the bottom of the bat, cut over square
defended on the front foot
cut to point
a push and run, good stuff from New Zealand there
outside off, fairly wide, gets away with it through a drive straight to cover
hint of room, McCullum clears the inner ring with a cover-drive - there was a signal of one short
up there, full on leg, hurried into the pads
another one of those unplayable Lee deliveries, so clean and fast
up there, the ball crashes into the pads, straight
the second wicket falls much the same as the first, another top-edged pull off Lee, with Gilchrist running round to his left and waiting for a while before pouching while shouting "Got him!"
drives down the wrong line to a tidy delivery
and a wide now...as the batsman moved across to off
not much... Lee bowling straight over the sticks, the batsman stepping back to try to get bat on it, but it's too quick
squares up and an outside edge rushes down to third man
defended off the back foot into the covers
outside off, cut into the off-side
a little bit of shape back into the right hander here, defended on the back foot
huge outside edge from a would-be cover drive goes up and over the slips, Lee runs round to tidy up
a miscue over midwicket for four, just caught the top edge of the hook there
great swing from Johnson, not a lot of shape in there, held its line there
another good delivery, pushed into the covers

...pretty well as it happens, getting a wicket first ball as that's chased round to Gilchrist who takes a lightning catch, first attempt two-handed overhead popped out, then he had to turn around to leap to take it one-handed just above the ground
decent delivery down off now
oops, a wide
too quick for Taylor, absolutely castled
tricksy swing away from the right hander
left alone outside off
right up there on off
wideish outside off, the batsman reaches out with a vain stab of a cut
beauty, carried on a full length, inducing the false drive, and Gilchrist took it at chest height
slower ball, Gilchrist admits he missed the signal from the bowler
worked off the legs to square
that was coming, a faint edge carries through to Gilchrist who takes yet another catch, this one just to his right
a very neat defence, Oram quickly in line
pushed off the hips for a quick single
slower delivery pushed across the left hander, who leaves it
across him again, flat-batted smash straight over Tait's head
pushed over the leg stump, short
straight, the batsman backs away, and steers an outside edge down towards first slip
outside off, too late on the shot to get any bat on it
pushed across the right hander, Styris drives but carves only air
outside off, Styris moves back and pushes off over point
outside off again, short, and Styris launches into that one, wide of long-off, over extra cover in fact
wide over leg
straight and short, the batsman backs away and cuts to gully, Clarke picks up and nearly shies down the non-striker's end
powers into a straight drive off the bottom of the bat, launching high, safe and just short of the rope
driven to mid-off where Bracken takes a tidy catch low to his left
pushed across the left hander, Oram driving just wide of cover, picking the gap well
a dab and run
pushed to cover
straight bouncer, Oram can only sway away from it
yorker, well dug into the leg-side
fast and straight bouncer
straight, and defended on the back foot
an unconvincing pull to square
short delivery again, well timed this time with a steer off the hips
cleans him up with the yorker and strikes in his first over for Australia, and not a bad victim, Vettori moving across his stumps and being bowled outside his legs
greets him with a bouncer
swings right on to the off stump line
a great shot, pulled in front of square, the batsman throwing out his front leg to give himself plenty of room to play
backs away, Lee following him outside leg, and dug out towards square
too good for the batsman, trapped in the crease, much as his feet are
straight bouncer again, the batsman can only sway away
nips in off the seam, forcing him to defend on the back foot
an inswinging yorker outside leg, the batsman jamming down at the last second
driven wide of Symonds on the long-off bouncary
driven out in the air towards mid-on and Johnson takes a great catch over his head, reaching out to grab it at the last second
round the wicket, a full toss creeps back into the batsman but it's left alone
outside off, pitches this time, driven out to long-off
straight over the batsman, who ducks at the last second
straight on leg, defended back down on the back foot
driven back past the bowler through mid-on
outside off, backed away and tried to cut
played wide of the slips, with some control
pushed right up there, Oram drives high and it plugs just inside the long-off boundary
tidy down the off-side line
bouncer over leg stump, Gilchrist forced to jump at a stretch to his right
big six over midwicket crashes into the boards
worked into the leg-side
driven out straight to long-off
dragged it down a touch, the batsman dropping his hands on it towards gully
outside off, driven over mid-off, Bracken fluffing it on the boundary
hooked over midwicket
driven wide of long-off this time, sent flat
Gillespie was well out courtesy of Symonds' underarm run out after pushing to cover, Oram sent him back
the ball clatters past him
straight bouncer, ducked under
another bouncer
driven towards mid-off
inswing on leg, pushed to midwicket for an easy single
massive six off the base of the bat over cover
pushed to the deep on the off side, they come back for two
straight six back over Symonds' head
Oram down on his knee and proposes to push round through fine, the ball bouncing off his pad
Symonds nearly had another run out as Oram's push back towards nearly ran up his partner Patel who was backing up a long way
there's no stopping him, Oram opening up again, this time with a towering on-drive over wide long-on
played straight over the keeper
Patel fails to get behind the ball this time, a bit of a windy whoosh
didn't get behind it that time either, backing away as Noffke cleaned him up to round off the match with three wickets, Oram's left stranded
